text: Lagunella is a genus of funnel weavers containing the single species, Lagunella guaycura. It was first described by J. Maya-Morales, M. L. Jiménez, G. Murugan & C. Palacios-Cardiel in 2017, and is only found in Mexico. ==References== ==External links== Category:Agelenidae Category:Monotypic Araneomorphae genera
title: Lagunella
